  "novel_contributions": [
    "We implement our findings into a simple self-supervised method, called DINO, which we interpret as a form of self-distillation with no labels.",
    "Self-supervised ViT features contain explicit information about the semantic segmentation of an image, which does not emerge as clearly with supervised ViTs, nor with convnets.",
    "These features are also excellent k-NN classifiers, reaching 78.3% top-1 on ImageNet with a small ViT.",
    "The study underlines the importance of momentum encoder, multi-crop training, and the use of small patches with ViTs.",
    "DINO is flexible and works on both convnets and ViTs without the need to modify the architecture, nor adapt internal normalizations."
  ],
  "key_claims": [
    {
      "claim": "Self-supervised ViT features explicitly contain scene layout and object boundaries, visible in the last-layer self-attention maps, unlike supervised ViTs or convnets.",
      "evidence_section": "Abstract",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "Self-supervised ViT features are strong k-NN classifiers, reaching 78.3% top-1 on ImageNet with a small ViT.",
      "evidence_section": "Abstract",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "DINO achieves 80.1% top-1 on ImageNet in linear evaluation with ViT-Base and small patches.",
      "evidence_section": "Abstract",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "DINO works on both convnets and ViTs, and matches the state of the art with a ResNet-50 architecture.",
      "evidence_section": "Abstract",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "Training DINO with ViT takes just two 8-GPU servers over 3 days to achieve 76.1% on ImageNet linear benchmark.",
      "evidence_section": "Introduction",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "Small patches improve performance substantially, and ViT-B/8 with DINO reaches 80.1% linear and 77.4% k-NN on ImageNet.",
      "evidence_section": "4.1. Comparing with SSL frameworks on ImageNet",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "Momentum encoder and multi-crop are crucial components for good DINO performance, while predictor and advanced normalization add little benefit.",
      "evidence_section": "5.1. Importance of the Different Components",
      "page": null
    },
    {
      "claim": "Centering and sharpening are complementary and both are needed to avoid collapse.",
      "evidence_section": "5.3. Avoiding collapse",
      "page": null
    }
  ]
